2 HOUSE BILL 1281
1 provider, there is a reasonable likelihood of the fetus’s sustained survival outside the womb.
2 (b) Except as PROVIDED IN § 20–210 OF THIS SUBTITLE OR AS otherwise
3 provided in this subtitle, the State may not interfere with the decision of a woman to
4 terminate a pregnancy:
5 (1) Before the fetus is viable; or
6 (2) At any time during the woman’s pregnancy, if:
7 (i) The termination procedure is necessary to protect the life or
8 health of the woman; or
9 (ii) The fetus is affected by genetic defect or serious deformity or
10 abnormality.
11 (c) The Department may adopt regulations that:
12 (1) Are both necessary and the least intrusive method to protect the life or
13 health of the woman; and
14 (2) Are not inconsistent with established clinical practice.
15 (d) The qualified provider is not liable for civil damages or subject to a criminal
16 penalty for a decision to perform an abortion under this section made in good faith and in
17 the qualified provider’s best clinical judgment in accordance with accepted standards of
18 clinical practice AND § 20–210 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
19 20–210.
20 (A) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A WOMAN SEEKING AN ABORTION IF:
21 (1) THE WOMAN IS THE VICTIM OF AN ALLEGED RAPE OR OF INCEST,
22 AS PROHIBITED UNDER § 3–323 OF THE CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE; AND
23 (2) THE INCIDENT OF RAPE OR INCEST IS REPORTED TO LAW
24 ENFORCEMENT.
25 (B) A QUALIFIED PROVIDER MAY NOT PERFORM OR INDUCE AN ABORTION
26 ON A PREGNANT WOMAN:
27 (1) WITHIN 24 HOURS AFTER THE WOMAN RECEIVES
28 TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (C)
29 OF THIS SECTION; OR

HOUSE BILL 1281 3
1 (2) IF THE WOMAN RESIDES AT LEAST 100 MILES FROM THE FACILITY
2 IN WHICH THE ABORTION WILL BE PERFORMED, WITHIN 2 HOURS AFTER THE
3 WOMAN RECEIVES TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING IN ACCORDANCE WITH
4 SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION.
5 (C) THE MEDICAL PROFESSIONAL PERFORMING THE TRANSABDOMINAL
6 ULTRASOUND IMAGING REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION MUST:
7 (1) BE TRAINED IN SONOGRAPHY AND WORKING UNDER THE
8 SUPERVISION OF A QUALIFIED PROVIDER;
9 (2) IF POSSIBLE, DETERMINE THE GESTATIONAL AGE OF THE FETUS
10 BASED ON:
11 (I) MEASUREMENT OF THE FETUS IN A MANNER CONSISTENT
12 WITH THE STANDARD OF CARE; OR
13 (II) IF ONLY THE GESTATIONAL SAC IS VISIBLE DURING THE
14 TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING, MEASUREMENT OF THE GESTATIONAL
15 SAC;
16 (3) IF GESTATIONAL AGE CANNOT BE DETERMINED UNDER ITEM (2)
17 OF THIS SUBSECTION, VERBALLY OFFER TO THE WOMAN OTHER ULTRASOUND
18 IMAGING TO DETERMINE GESTATIONAL AGE OF THE FETUS;
19 (4) IF PRESENT AND VIEWABLE, INCLUDE IN THE ULTRASOUND
20 IMAGE:
21 (I) THE DIMENSIONS OF THE FETUS; AND
22 (II) AN ACCURATE PORTRAYAL OF THE PRESENCE OF
23 EXTERNAL MEMBERS AND INTERNAL ORGANS OF THE FETUS;
24 (5) MAKE A PRINT OF THE ULTRASOUND IMAGE TO DOCUMENT ANY
25 MEASUREMENTS TAKEN TO DETERMINE THE GESTATIONAL AGE OF THE FETUS;
26 (6) VERBALLY OFFER TO THE WOMAN DURING THE
27 TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING THE OPTION TO:
28 (I) VIEW THE ULTRASOUND IMAGE;
29 (II) RECEIVE A PRINTED COPY OF THE ULTRASOUND IMAGE;
30 AND

4 HOUSE BILL 1281
1 (III) HEAR THE FETAL HEARTBEAT IN A MANNER CONSISTENT
2 WITH THE STANDARD OF CARE; AND
3 (7) OBTAIN FROM THE WOMAN WRITTEN CERTIFICATION THAT:
4 (I) THE MEDICAL PROFESSIONAL PERFORMING THE
5 TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING OFFERED OPTIONS AS REQUIRED UNDER
6 ITEM (6) OF THIS SUBSECTION; AND
7 (II) IF APPLICABLE, THE WOMAN RESIDES AT LEAST 100 MILES
8 FROM THE FACILITY IN WHICH THE ABORTION WILL BE PERFORMED.
9 (D) A WOMAN IS NOT REQUIRED TO ACCEPT ANYTHING OFFERED DURING
10 TRANSABDOMINAL ULTRASOUND IMAGING PERFORMED IN ACCORDANCE WITH
11 SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, INCLUDING OFFERS MADE UNDER SUBSECTION
12 (C)(3) AND (6) OF THIS SECTION.
13 (E) THE FACILITY IN WHICH AN ABORTION IS PERFORMED SHALL MAINTAIN
14 A PRINTED COPY OF THE ULTRASOUND IMAGE MADE UNDER SUBSECTION (C)(5) OF
15 THIS SECTION FOR THE GREATER OF:
16 (1) 7 YEARS; OR
17 (2) AN AMOUNT OF TIME AS REQUIRED BY FEDERAL OR STATE LAW.
18 (F) A QUALIFIED PROVIDER WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS SUBJECT TO A
19 PENALTY OF UP TO $2,500.
20 (G) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO PROHIBIT A QUALIFIED
21 PROVIDER FROM USING ULTRASOUND IMAGING THAT THE QUALIFIED PROVIDER
22 CONSIDERS MEDICALLY APPROPRIATE, CONSISTENT WITH THE STANDARD OF CARE.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
24 October 1, 2026.

